SIMPLE: worthiness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Worthiness
<hw>Wor"thi*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state of being
worthy; desert; merit; excellence; dignity; virtue; worth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Who is sure he hath a soul, unless⟦br⟧
It see, and judge, and follow <qex>worthiness</qex>?</q>
<rj><qau>Donne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She is not worthy to be loved that hath not some feeling of her
own <qex>worthiness.</qex></q> <rj><qau>Sir P. Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The prayers which our Savior made were for his own
<qex>worthiness</qex> accepted.</q> <rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Worthless</ent>⟦br⟧
